                            <comment id="12646694" author="phunt" created="Tue, 11 Nov 2008 22:17:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;add resonable wait times for event polling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In some cases the poll was expected to not return results (depending on args to the function) and in other cases it was expecting. I suspect the short poll times were to shorten the run time of the test (re no result expected). I moved to 10seconds to handle this, short enough to let the test run in resonable time, long enough to handle slowness in the system (cpu/disk loading outside zk, etc...)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12648424" author="mahadev" created="Tue, 18 Nov 2008 00:09:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for the patch ... the tests pass &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
